properties.name: Big Ben
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman47london, egnland The Largest Four face clock in the world , located in the United kingdom. The iron faces are set up in 23 foot diameter. The clock is honored for its reliability. The name Big Ben was given to a 16 ton bell , known as the great bell. The clock is a focus on New Year celebrations , and other holidays. Big Ben has become a symbol for the United kingdom and London. This clock has been used in a lot of movies such as hairy potter, peter pan , Shanghai Knights and ext...

properties.name: Eiffle Tower
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman47Paris, France This iron tower has become an icon for France. The eiffle tower was first built for an entrance to a world fair . So 18,000 peices of iron later, the eiffle tower was built.

properties.name: Great Wall of China
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman47China The great wall of China was originally built for their protection. The Great Wall of China is 3,107 miles long . The Chinese were familiar with wall building by the time of spring and autumn period. Their Main threat were the Mongolians, but the Chinese had smart tactics and built a giant wall to keep them out. Also had their wepons such as fire works. Which used black gun powder , do launch missles toward their enemies.

properties.name: My Home
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman471706 williams road , 33565 This is were i have been staying for the past 8 years. I like this place i call home because it is in the country. That has its benefits that i can do stuff that i can do with close neighbors. My grandpa built the house before we lived in it. My house is green and white on the outside , and is a man layer. Its just me , dad , and my brother.

properties.name: burj dubai
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman47dubai This is the worlds tallest skyscraper. It is located beside the Dubai desert. it surpasses 2,300 feet. In American money it cost 900 million. It is twice the size of the empire state building. America is at highest in economy, but the middle east now has the highest building.

properties.name: charolston
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman47south carolina One of the oldest cities , started in 1670 and still in the same place. It is also the fifth largest city in America. Also known as the Holy city due to the amount of small churches. Named after King Charles the 2nd of England. It was recognized as the most calm city in 1995. It is very interesting to have something so old still around.

properties.name: grand canyon
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman47arizona The Grand Canyon was believed to be formed by the Colorado River . Then formed a gorge by the currents. This is a huge tourist attraction for America. It became a national monument in 1908 for tourist. Also for natural reason , and for conservation. Lots of minerals are found in the Grand canyon , such as limestone.

The tomb was not found in an area were royalty was usually buried. An Egyptian Pharaoh of the eighteenth dynasty. his name translates * living image of At en.

properties.name: mount everest
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman47argentina Measuring at 29,000 it is easily the worlds tallest mountain. There has been a total of 210 deaths on this mountain.It can cost up to 25,000$ per person to get a permit to climb the mountain. In 1980 Messier reached the top of the mountain. For the first time in history. now it is a huge tourist attraction in Argentina.

properties.name: twin towers
properties.description: Posted by Gstheman47new york city The twin towers at one time were the tallest buildings in America. On September 11th , something went wrong. A plane was high jacked. Then was ran into the perfect spot to make the building fall. In America it is a moment we will always remember. It was the first civilian attack in the US. Witch sparked the war with Iraq.
